Hi.  I ftp'ed Abtweak a few days ago with an eye toward using it for a
image processing planner we are developing here.  After running the
planner on some of the small test problems, it seemed kinda slow to me
(60 sec for the 3 ring hanoi problem.)  When I ran abtweak through the
profiler, I found there was one function (transitive-test-before-p)
that took almost all of the processor time.  So I reprogrammed it in
two different ways; the first seems to be faster (about 15 sec) on
small examples and also a bit neater; whereas the second is based on
what I think is a better algorithm, although it seems to be taking a
little longer (18 sec or so).  Anyway, here they are.  If I have the
inclination and time I might write a graph sweep-and-mark algorithm to
improve this business even more.

